text: Nicky Nieves is an American sitting volleyball player. She played at the 2016 Summer Paralympics, winning a gold medal, 2014 ParaVolley World Championships, 2018 ParaVolley World Championships, and 2019 Parapan American Games. She was born in the Bronx in New York City. She studied speech pathology in Queens College, City University of New York. == References == Category:Living people Category:Year of birth missing (living people) Category:American sitting volleyball players Category:Paralympic gold medalists for the United States Category:Sportspeople from the Bronx
